#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:1
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:3
msgid ""
"Different problems that can occur on a new instance, and how to solve them."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:5
msgid ""
"Many Lemmy features depend on a correct reverse proxy configuration. Make "
"sure yours is equivalent to our [nginx config](https://github.com/LemmyNet/"
"lemmy-ansible/blob/main/templates/nginx.conf)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:7
msgid "General"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:9
msgid "Logs"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:11
msgid ""
"For frontend issues, check the [browser console](https://webmasters."
"stackexchange.com/a/77337) for any error messages."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:13
msgid ""
"For server logs, run `docker compose logs -f lemmy` in your installation "
"folder. You can also do `docker compose logs -f lemmy lemmy-ui pictrs` to "
"get logs from different services."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:15
msgid ""
"If that doesn't give enough info, try changing the line `RUST_LOG=error` in "
"`docker-compose.yml` to `RUST_LOG=info` or `RUST_LOG=trace`, then do `docker "
"compose restart lemmy`."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:17
msgid "Creating admin user doesn't work"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:19
msgid ""
"Make sure that websocket is working correctly, by checking the browser "
"console for errors. In nginx, the following headers are important for this:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:21
msgid ""
"```\n"
"proxy_http_version 1.1;\n"
"proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;\n"
"proxy_set_header Connection \"upgrade\";\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:27
msgid "Rate limit error when many users access the site"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:29
msgid ""
"Check that the headers `X-Real-IP` and `X-Forwarded-For` are sent to Lemmy "
"by the reverse proxy. Otherwise, it will count all actions towards the rate "
"limit of the reverse proxy's IP. In nginx it should look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:37
msgid "Federation"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:39
msgid "Other instances can't fetch local objects (community, post, etc)"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:41
msgid ""
"Your reverse proxy (eg nginx) needs to forward requests with header `Accept: "
"application/activity+json` to the backend. This is handled by the following "
"lines:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:43
msgid ""
"```\n"
"set $proxpass \"http://0.0.0.0:{{ lemmy_ui_port }}\";\n"
"if ($http_accept = \"application/activity+json\") {\n"
"set $proxpass \"http://0.0.0.0:{{ lemmy_port }}\";\n"
"}\n"
"if ($http_accept = \"application/ld+json; profile=\\\"https://www.w3.org/ns/"
"activitystreams\\\"\") {\n"
"set $proxpass \"http://0.0.0.0:{{ lemmy_port }}\";\n"
"}\n"
"proxy_pass $proxpass;\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:54
msgid ""
"You can test that it works correctly by running the following commands, all "
"of them should return valid JSON:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:56
msgid ""
"```\n"
"curl -H \"Accept: application/activity+json\" https://your-instance.com/u/"
"some-local-user\n"
"curl -H \"Accept: application/activity+json\" https://your-instance.com/c/"
"some-local-community\n"
"curl -H \"Accept: application/activity+json\" https://your-instance.com/"
"post/123 # the id of a local post\n"
"curl -H \"Accept: application/activity+json\" https://your-instance.com/"
"comment/123 # the id of a local comment\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:63
msgid ""
"Fetching remote objects works, but posting/commenting in remote communities "
"fails"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:65
msgid ""
"Check that [federation is allowed on both instances]"
"(federation_getting_started.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:67
msgid ""
"Also ensure that the time is correct on your server. Activities are signed "
"with a timestamp, and will be discarded if it is off by more than one hour."
msgstr ""

