#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:122
msgid "You don't receive actions reliably"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:124
msgid ""
"Due to the lemmy queue, remote lemmy instances will be sending apub sync "
"actions serially to you. If your server rate of processing them is slower "
"than the rate the origin server is sending them, when visiting the [lemmy-"
"federation-state](https://phiresky.github.io/lemmy-federation-state/site) "
"for the remote server, you'll see your instance in the \"lagging behind\" "
"section."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:126
msgid ""
"This can be avoided by setting the config value `federation."
"concurrent_sends_per_instance` to a value greater than 1 on the sending "
"instance."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:128
msgid ""
"Typically the speed at which you process an incoming action should be less "
"than 100ms. If this is higher, this might signify problems with your "
"database performance or your networking setup."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:130
msgid ""
"Note that even apub action ingestion speed which seems sufficient for most "
"other instances, might become insufficient if the origin server is receiving "
"actions from their userbase faster than you can process them. I.e. if the "
"origin server receives 10 actions per second, but you can only process 8 "
"actions per second, you'll inevitably start falling behind that one server "
"only."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:132
msgid "These steps might help you diagnose this."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:134
msgid "Check processing time on the loadbalancer"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:136
msgid ""
"Check how long a request takes to process on the backend. In haproxy for "
"example, the following command will show you the time it takes for apub "
"actions to complete"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:139
msgid "\"POST \\/inbox\""
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:142
msgid ""
"[See here for nginx](https://www.nginx.com/blog/using-nginx-logging-for-"
"application-performance-monitoring/)"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:144
msgid ""
"If these actions take more than 100ms, you might want to investigate deeper."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:146
msgid "Check your Database performance"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:148
msgid "Ensure that it's not very high in CPU or RAM utilization."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:150
msgid ""
"Afterwards check for slow queries. If you regularly see common queries with "
"high max and mean exec time, it might signify your database is struggling. "
"The below SQL query will show you all queries (you will need "
"`pg_stat_statements` [enabled](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/"
"pgstatstatements.html))"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:157
msgid ""
"If you see very high time on inserts, you might want to consider disabling "
"`synchronous_commit` to see if this helps."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:159
msgid "Check your backend performance."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:161
msgid ""
"Like the DB, if the server where your lemmy rust backend is running is "
"overloaded, you might see such an impact"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:163
msgid "Check your Network Layout"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:165
msgid ""
"If your backend and database appear to be in good condition, it might be "
"that your issue is network based."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:167
msgid ""
"One problem can occur is your backend and your database are not in the same "
"server and are too far from each other in geographic location. Due to the "
"amount of DB queries performed for each apub sync request, even a small "
"amount of latency can quickly add up."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:169
msgid "Check the latency between your rust backend and your DB using ping"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:175
msgid ""
"if the `time` you see if above 1-2ms, this can start causing such delays. In "
"that case, you might want to consider moving your backend closer to your DB "
"geographically, so that your latency is below 2ms"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:177
msgid ""
"Note that your external loadbalancer(s) (if any) do not necessarily need to "
"be closer to the DB, as they do not do multiple small DB requests."
msgstr ""

